  "text": "Cats of either sex weighing 3-4 kg were sedated with ketamine (11 mg/kg im) and anesthetized with pento- [CITATION_1] . Perfusion pressure was 90-110 Torr. After muscle dissection, the cats were killed with pentobarbital. Perfused muscles were attached to a force transducer and platinum stimulation electrodes in a specially designed 7.4-cm-diam NMR probe that is otherwise similar to the 5-cm probe described previously [CITATION_2] . Muscle length and stimulation voltage were adjusted to produce maximum twitch force, and temperature was maintained at 37 ± 2°C during the experiments.",
